messages.content: What are some technical specs in this submittal?

This document discusses the technical specifications and performance characteristics of USG Sheetrock® Brand Abuse-Resistant Products, focusing on their durability and resistance to various types of damage in institutional settings.
- The panels are classified into four performance categories: Moderate Duty Areas, Medium Duty Areas, Heavy Duty Areas, and Extreme Duty Areas, each designed for specific levels of impact and abrasion resistance.
- Installation techniques for the panels include conventional wallboard methods, with a fire-resistant gypsum core encased in 100% recycled face and back papers.
- Testing standards include ASTM C1629 for abuse resistance, ASTM D4977 for abrasion resistance, and ASTM D5420 for indentation resistance, ensuring compliance with industry requirements.
- The Sheetrock® AR Firecode® Core Gypsum Panels are a basic upgrade from standard 5/8" Type X panels, while the Mold Tough® AR panels offer enhanced moisture and mold resistance.
- The Mold Tough® VHI panels feature fiberglass mesh for improved impact resistance, suitable for heavy- to extreme-duty applications.
Source: sheetrock-abuse-resistant-gypsum-panels-products-selector-guide-en-WB2553.pdf, section 0
